    'topic' => 'Imperial Stagnation',
    'body' => 'Dear Folks -

Aaron DaMommio said:

>What is harder to explain is how the Imperium has lagged at TL15 for so long,

I think you\'ll find that the real reason is  *player* reason rather than one
that was deliberately thought out for the *characters* and the game\'s background
history:

1. Regina was the first published sector. As such, it was on the border, and had
few high-tech worlds. Regina (the capital) was only TL 10, and the highest was
TL 13 (Pixie). For a character to acquire a TL 15 item was like a fantasy PC
finding a magic item - "wow, just look at this u-beaut thingy!"

2. When the Marches was published, GDW decided that TL 13 was "average Imperial
tech level" - it was the TL 15 planets that were anomalies. Just like that TL 17
world in the Regency, they couldn\'t advance any further - "who wants to buy
a high-tech gadget if you have to travel back 2 subsectors to fix it when it
breaks?"

3. When the Atlas of the Imperium was published, along with all that Library
Data (A-M, N-Z), the reason for the Imperial stagnation at TL 15 was never
really explained in terms of the background. "I mean, gee, the Imperium is at a
higher TL than all of surrounding space - what more do you want?"

4. The "game balance" POV - an example of *player* reasons - is to prevent PC\'s
from winding up with TL 21 Wave Motion Guns when even the Impi Navy only had
what was available at TL 15. This has not prevented one of my players from
desperately wanting a set of TL 17 mimetic battle dress, of course - it just
means that acquiring such an item means much searching, travelling, NPC
interaction - in short, ADVENTURING!! (which is what it is all about).

- Hyphen
(David Jaques-Watson)

