David P. Summers said:

>I\'ve been running a bunch of the old Classic Traveller adventures...
>Are there any adventures published that are set in the 5FW?

Offhand:

1. The _Spinward Marches Campaign_ contains a 5FW adventure, as well as details
of how the GDW version of the war panned out.

2. Early _Journals of the Travellers Aid Society_ (from issue #9, "War!"
onwards!) have a few scenarios set in or near the 5FW:
- "A Dagger At Efate" (#8?), just prior to the war;
- "77th Patron", where an Imp spy hands the Zho war plans to the PC\'s, prior
to the war;
- "Soft Bunk, or What To Do When The Zho\'s Invade";
- one set on Quar or Ruby or something, where an Imp archealogical team are
captured when the Zho\'s invade;
- two articles giving breakdowns on Zho and Impy troop organisations;
- a scenario involving the invasion of Vilis or Garda-Vilis (probably more to
do with the Sword Worlds than the Zho\'s (maybe this _is_ "Soft Bunk"??!);
- Striker II contains a scenario on Efate, during the height of the 5FW battle
for the world;
..um, I don\'t have my article list here, does anyone have any more?

3. _Adventure ?: Broadsword_ contained some scenarios involving Zhos during
the 5FW, especially on Garda-Vilis;

4. Alien Races (title?) had a post-5FW scenario where the PC\'s had to convince
some Zho\'s that the war was over (very Japanese-soldier-on-Pacific-island sort
of stuff).

Well, that\'s all I can think of so far. ;-)

- Hyphen
(David Jaques-Watson)

