    'date' => 'Fri, 5 Jan 1996 01:10:27 +1100 (EST)',
    'day' => '05',
    'index' => 'ac261',
    'topic' => 'Technology - What\'s Wrong With Traveller\'s Rating System',
    'body' => 'Several people have been commenting on the Traveller tech rating system, and
some interesting comments have been made; however, I believe that the *real*
problem has been missed (or, perhaps, it\'s been done to death in previous
Xboat "issues"?)

What is the "real" problem? Well, there are several, and I\'m not going to go
into all, or into the ones I do in great detail, but --

1) Let\'s consider "Personal Military Technology", pp. 26-27, MTrav Referee\'s
Companion.

TL/5 (c. 1930) = bolt action rifle, explosive hand grenades in widespread use
TL/6 (c. 1950) = semiauto rifle supersedes BA rifle, carbine, SMG and auto
                 pistol achieve wide military use
TL/7 (c. 1970) = assault rifle becomes main military weapon; grenade launchers
                 appear
TL/8 (c. 1990) = AR remains main weapon, RAM grenades appear, laser carbine
                 appears
TL/9 (c. 2010) = Laser rifles appear
TL/10 (c. 2100) = Advanced Combat Rifle, firing RAM grenade, appears

Now, let us consider this. What is the difference between a BA Rifle (say the
Lee Enfield .303 or the Mauser KAR-98k) and a Semiauto Rifle (like, say, the
Garand or the Gewehr 43) and between them and an Assault Rifle (like, say,
the MP/43-44) and between them and a SMG (like, say, the MP-38 or PPsh-43 or
M-3)? Apart from the fact that *all* were used reasonably widely in WW2, some
interesting facts should be noted -

* BA Rifles are *more* expensive, and actually take *higher* technology to
produce than ARs and SMGs!!! They require expensive high-tech (for the time)
*machining* of parts - ARs such are usually made from stamped parts (and, note,
the MP-43/44 series is still around today ... as the AK-47/74!!!).

* SMGs are even *cheaper* to produce, and take even *less* technology than an
AR. Take the Sten, it was produced in bicycle workshops by the Brits, and in
backyard "factories" by the Maquis in occupied France.

What we havem of course, is *not* a description of *technology* but of
*invention chronology*. There is a vast, and important, difference. There
is, in fact, no reason why a TL/4 culture (say around the period of the US
Civil War) could not produce a Sten or an AK. The only requirement is that
it has achieved an industrial culture with the required machine tools. And,
yep, they had \'em at that time. What they did *not* have was anyone who
actually came up with the *idea* of a Sten or AK. So, in fact, TL/4-5-6-7-8
and even the mechanical components of TL/10 ACRs, are *really* TL/4 *AS FAR
AS TECHNOLOGY NEEDED TO PRODUCE THEM IS CONCERNED*

Again, look at Energy (pg. 29) -

TL/4 (pre 1930) = Steam Engines
TL/5 (c. 1930) = Hydrocarbon fuel and Internal combustion engines

then

TL/9 (c. 2010) = Primitive Fusion Plants
TL/10 (c. 2100) = 2000 l. min Fusion Plants
TL/11 = 1000 l. minimum Fusion Plants
TL/12 = 250 l. minimum Fusion Plants
TL/13 = Fusion Output = 3kw per l.
TL/14 = 100 l. minimum Fusion Plants
TL/15 = Fusion Output = 6kw per l.
TL/16 = 80 liter minimum Fusion Plant

OK, why are Fusion Plants - obviously only capable of incremental improvement
from TL/9 to TL/16 treated as *eight* TLs, while External/Internal Combustion
engines are treated as only two. Surely there should be separate TLs, on the
basis of the treatment of Fusion Plants, for Savery Engines, Newcomen Engines,
Watt Engines, High Pressure Steam, Forced Draught Steam, Steam Turbines,
Early Petrol, Diesel, Wankel Rotary, Electronic Fuel Control, Ceramic Engines
and all the rest.

Nope, what it boils down to is the whole TL system is a crock. It always has
been and there is no way that it can be made to work (and, yes, I tried when
i co-wrote "Space Opera" many years ago), simply because it focuses on the
wrong things.

The only solution is to look at a planet\'s technological *capability* - if
they have machine tools, then they *can* make all those neat weapons from
BA Rifles through to ARs and ACRs (maybe not the electronics of the latter).
They may *not*, but that does *not* mean that they cannot!

It\'s like I suggested in an earlier post here (or was it to the Traveller
list?) - the whole system (and there are clues scattered throughout all the
pre-TNE stuff) is a deliberately artificial construct of the Imperial Govt
which wishes to keep technology from spreading. The main fear of a vilani
dominated Imperium (and the Vilani really won the Nth Interstellar War when
they manipulated Estigarribia into his treason! Again, the evidence is all
there!) is that technology will get out of control before society (and the
Emperor and Imperial Nobles who, of course, control it - oh, and don\'t
forget the Megacorps; either Vilani, or Terran ones that supported the traitor)
is "ready" to accpet it. In other words, they want to make damn sure that
hi-tech doesn\'t spread too fast because it might stunt their little protection
racket - which is all the Imperium is! The Imperium manipulates whole planets
and whole societies (as we know from their manipulation of Psionics), and, in
this case, they are manipulating them into thinking that quite simple progress-
ions in tech ability are somehow vastly difficult because they are a "new TL"!

Well, at least you can make a quite good case for all the above. And it
certainly does explain the rubbish that is the Traveller TL system!

Phil McGregor


