    'body' => '

> I\'ve been running a bunch of the old Classic Traveller adventures.
> Lately, I\'ve been thinking about bringing about the Fifth Frontier
> War.  However, I don\'t want it to be just something that happens.
> Are there any adventures published that are set in the 5th Front.
> War?

The Spinward Marches Campaign describes the progress of the war from 1107 to
1110. It details the belligerents and it provides maps showing the war
\'fronts\' at six-month intervals throughout the war.

It also includes material drawn from \'Citizens of the Imperium\'. The
adventure included in The Spinward Marches Campaign actually takes place
immediately after the war (as is the adventure from \'Alien Realms\', which
was mentioned here).

More useful to you are the majority of Amber Zone articles in JTAS from
issue #9 (the war issue) to around issue #22 or #23.

The FFW boardgame is, of course, a must.

The outcome of the pre-war adventure \'Twilight\'s Peak\' may have a marked
effect on the Zhodani conduct of the war.

My advice is to work out what your players will find most interesting and
design your adventures around that.

For example, the first time I ran a FFW campaign, the characters started at
Lysen in the middle of a Zhodani attack. They escaped that and enlisted as
soon as they reached safety. They then ran with a convoy to Darrian, and
then on to the Five Sisters Subsector where they spent most of the rest of
the war foiling spy plots and administering Imperial policy.

For my second FFW campaign, the players were interested in shoot-em-up
adventures. So, after reading about the SBS Agean Campaign during WWII, I
set up a small commando-style hit & run unit, and my players spent the
majority of the war blowing things up and shooting people.

In my current FFW campaign, which has just started, the players are
merchants who are trying to trade in the demilitarised zone between the Zho
and the Imperium (i.e. that blank area around Arden). I am also running a
TCS PBEM set in this area, where the players each have small commerce-raider
type groups.

If you have any questions, please email me directly (dave_elrick@ps.co.uk)
or on this list (it might tempt others to give it a try) and I\'ll try to
help.

Kind Regards

Dave Elrick

