They *did* build them! The remains of some sort of geared calculating
device were found underwater near some Greek island some years back.
It\'s thought it was used for astronomical work.

Another example is that there\'s evidence (not widely accepted) that
electroplating was known in Mesopotamia!

The problem is that until you get to things like printing, and
especially *patents*, people have a distinct advantage in keeping
inventions *secret*. So it\'s easy for them to be lost.

