get T:TNE, because I bought it from Dave Nilsen in person the day they were
packing the boxes for shipment to distributors.]  According to what I was
told, a large part of Marc Miller\'s thinking was financial -- he could do a
much better job sending his kids through college as an insurance salesman than
as a game designer.  He remained a major stockholder, though, and continued to
be a member of the board (at least at that time).

I am very encouraged so many people are jumping in to rescue Traveller.  I
wonder if Marc Miller (who is getting the rights back) and Steve Jackson (who
has the resources) would get together...

SJG wanted to do a GURPS:Traveller years ago (around when TNE came out) but
GDW wasn\'t interested.


Christopher Weuve  [caw@intercon.com]
