I almost agree with you.  My take on this would be that if a new rules
system is created, have an appendix in the main rule book.  In the
appendix there would be rules for converting between the current
edition and any of the previous editions.  This would also allow
players to convert between MT and new version, TNE to MT, etc...  If
it is really expansive, then it could also include ways to convert
most vehicle stats (a quick fix), as well as include ways to convert
from other sci-fi games to/from Traveller.  The last idea I\'ve seen
done in such games as Nexus and Over The Edge.  Fantastic idea!  Allow
people to purchase the background source if that\'s all they\'re
interested in and let them use their current system (or find out how
much they\'re missing and convert to ours. 8)

But then again, I think that a GURPS Traveller sourcebook (in
addition to the Marc Miller stuff) wouldn\'t be a bad idea.

