    'body' => 'Phillip McGregor writes:
>However, the main problem is that there was only a one TL difference between
>the competitors ... the Terrans achieved Jump3 while the Vilani had only
>Jump2.
>
>Looking along the same TL lines, Jump3 is TL12 and Jump2 TL 11.

Steve Higginbotham once calculated that TL 12 navies have a 2/1 advantage
over TL 11 navies. Of course, this assumes that both parties build sensible
ships. If the Vilani were used to being the ones with the TL advantage then
their ships may not have been optimally designed at first. It\'s hard to
imagine that they wouldn\'t improve once they had some serious competition,
though.

He also mentions that when you go from a straight strength comparison you
can shift those odds by 1-100 depending on the strategies.

However, as has already been raised as a posibility, Vilani turncoats could
change the odds a lot. Add Vilani divisiveness, with provincial admirals
revolting against the Shadow Emperor, and you may have an explanation that
holds water.



