    'day' => '28',
    'topic' => 'Jump Torpedoes: The Last Word?',
    'body' => 'Just checking through FF&S, and the *only* restriction that I can find there
for the design of Jump Capable vessels is in the Jump Drive section, where
it states that the *minimum* size JDrive is 2 cubic meters. Just slightly
larger than what is needed to give a 2 ton Torpedo/Drone/Missile Jump-6!

So, it\'s official in Leviathan, implied by the way Black Globes work as noted
in High Guard and MTrav (and by how JDrives work in Starship Operators Manual)
and now its official in TNE. Says it all. And as most people seem to realise,
it is *not* going to be a threat to the XBoat net, or civilisation as we know
it!

