    'from' => 'David P. Summers',
    'topic' => 'Jump Torps vs Xboats',
    'body' => '>I agree. In fact it is likely that if j-torps were to be introduced it would
>be by the X-Boat Service itself in order to service the areas off the main
>X-Boat routes. Considering the way business is done in the Trav universe,
>particularly on the frontiers, one would expect that contestability in the
>interstellar communication market to be very low. One would expect any
>competitor putting itself up against the X-Boat Service, a service of the
>Imperium, would be quickly delt with.
>
>So long as the jump time, which is so critical to the fundamental game
>mechanics, remains the same for the j-torp,  I see no problem.
>One would have to expect greater losses through misjump with j-torps, however.

Whether or not Jump Torpedos completely eliminate the X-boat network
(and they will, at least, margninalize it) one has to face that they
significantly change the character of the setting.  No long do
you have to risk taking ships into a system to communicate.  No
longer do you need to maintain a network of Jump 6 ships to have
jump 6 communications.  Look at he timeline for the death of Stephon
and the Rebellion, torps would significantly alter thaty.

The Traveller setting is based on difficult comunications.  The
attractions of jump torpedoes is that they make communications easier.
For that reason they have to fundamentally change the setting.

