    'body' => 'At 12:47 PM 2/02/96 -0500, you wrote:
>Hi there,
>
>My question concerns a conversion between starship damage and some of
>the 10D+ damages that can be achieved from weapons in Book 4: Mercenary.
>Starship damage is done in "hits" (i.e. each laser that hit gets to
>role once on the "hit location" table of Book 2, missles get 1D6 "hits"
>and High Gaurd has other tables).  Is there any official (or working
>unofficial) method to determine how many pts of damage (e.g. 16D)
>constitues a "hit" if the weapon is used to fire at a starship.
>If anyone has any workable scheme on this I\'d like to hear it.
>

There are a couple ways you could do this:
        1) Apply/adapt the MT damage rules (which did give vehicle hit
tables and damage ratings for vehicles up to and including sarships)

        2) Adapt the rules from Robots (Book 8).  For the ship as a whole
and for each part that will take damage follow the following steps:
                a.determine volume in liters (13,500 liters/disp. ton)
                b.divide this number by 5 to get the points of damage it can
take before becoming inoperative (minimum 1 pt)
                c.divide the same number by 2 to get the points of damage it
can take before it is destroyed (minimum 1 pt)

Note that method #2 will give you ships *much* more sturday than #1--by a
factor of 10, I believe.

I hope this is helpful.

