    'file' => 'XBOAT96/XBT96526.TXT',
    'year' => 1996,
    'from' => 'Alun Moon A.J.Moon@newcastle.ac.uk',
    'body' => 'One thing I have noticed in the recent thread, is that people are mixing
rules systems when trying to "justify" their position.

The j-torps originally came from Leviathan (CT), in the ensuing debate
rules from CT, MT, and TNE have been thrown about.  Much to my confusion.

Myself I\'ve never even got hold of the MT rules, let alone the TNE rules,
so references to them are difficult to follow.

I do remember haveing a go with the MT ship construction rules, I tried
putting a Type-S together, and found I needed something like 8500 cubic
meters of fuel - in a 1400 cubic meter ship!

This is not to critisise the MT rules, the construction rules were a good
attempt to try to use a single system.

Being a fan of CT, and sticking to this system, I try to avoid having to
resort to MT and other sources, as I find they do mess a few things up.

Perhapse its best said that there is going to be no *one*definitive*
answer to all this, and that its up to the referee as to the details of
"his" universe.  Mine looks like a cross between Star Trek (TNG),
Alien(s), and a few other sources for imagary.

Its very usefull to see how other people run their games, but not usefull
to say "that\'s wrong... In *my* game...".

Its good to be able to put ideas up here to get comments on them, but
they are always going to be in the context of that referees "house
universe", so not completely apparent why hes done particular things.

So..
Keep talking, and keep on Travelling

Alun
