    'from' => 'Harley Grantham',
    'topic' => 'Achitecture of the Future',
    'body' => 'A change of subject from the ever popular J-torps. :)

I have been giving some thought to what cities and other structures would look
like in the Traveller Universe.  How would some of the high tech buildings
look once contragravity became available, and then common.  How would the
Zhodani architecture differ from the Imperial?

I really don\'t like the way much of this has been portrayed in Traveller,
although some of the Megatraveller supplements have some interesting struc-
tures on their covers.  The Imperial palace is a massive floating sphere.
Dull. Dull, Dull, Dull!   I would think once technology can free architects
from the laws of physics, they would let there imaginations soar, not revert
to simple shapes that are easy for non-artists to draw.  (Which seems to have
been a major factor in Traveller descriptions.)

The space docks in Star Trek films and on Babylon 5 are much more interesting
than the boring sphere described in one of the DGP magazines, (I think it
was the MT Journal).  And the floating city in Empire Strikes Back was
the sort of thing I would expect on some of the more exotic atmosphere worlds.

So the bottom line is I cannot turn to the tradtional Traveller sources and
expect to find anything interesting.  I think this is a major deficency with
Traveller, as this is the sort of thing that can really add color to a game.
My single biggest problem with Traveller has been the lack of descriptions
for alien worlds that give a feel for that alieness.

So does anyone have any references, suggestions, wild ideas?

Thanks for your time.

--
Harley Granthamgranthh@anubis.network.com
