>Travellers\' Digest) which stated that by increasing the time spent
>making the jump calculations, a fleet could reduce the spread of its
>ships when they came out of J-space.

Actually, in CT multiple ships could jump in perfect synchronization.
When DGP added the variability to the jump times, someone
eventually pointed out the "scatter" problem for fleets and
convoys, and so DGP and Marc Miller came up with the
"incease jump-calc time" solution.

The fleet (with respect to "real" time) still has that circa 2 days
variability in jump breakout, but with respect to the other ships
in that fleet scatter time is reduced to about an hour.


