    'index' => 'ac669',
    'topic' => ' XBOAT digest 541',
    'body' => 'RE$ Lance\'s Nobility Issue:

Your idea is basically similar to published cannon. However, unlanded
titles are able to be passed on and draw no monies. The landed nobles are
also not the same as positional nobles, whose title is based upon the
position they hold, which includes all planetary rulers, sector and
subsector dukes, and Domain Archdukes.

Hans & I have been debating this privately of late.
I suggest maintaining the cannonical structure, which has math working out
a bit high from CGen tables (3-5% of population in nobility, and almost as
many knights).

the three types of noble (paraphrased from Library Data(N-Z))

>Service: Awarded for brownnosing the emperor, or mabey a duke or an archduke.
>Get lands, get suppport
>
>Achievement: Get Title, no other benefits. Much like modern brittish knights.
>
>Positional: Get title while in office only.
>
>Note that all types could be enfeoffed (landed), but only service nobles
>routinely get lands. A Service title could be landless. Service and
>achievement
>titles are hereditary. Positional titles could carry some perpetual title as a
>reward for service, which would be a service title.

I agree with giving enfeoffed nobles the ability to draw revenue from a
starport.

-Wil

William F. Hostman

