    'body' => 'Alvin Plummer <alvin.plummer@sheridanc.on.ca>, ed, 21 Feb 1996

>I never really followed the Jump torp debate, because of prior demands on
>my "Traveller Time" and a cowardly need to avoid heated arguments.

Probably a wise decision.

>However, I would be interested to hear how the argument boils down to,
>like the Great Feudal Technocracy Debate ("You can define it anyway you
>choose") and the Fabulous Jump Rock-Throwing Contest ("You can\'t stop
>jump rocks at velocity").

I\'m not sure what you want.  The main disagreement, for me at least,
is...Is the presence of ability to send messages through jump
space, in small portable "torpedoes", consistent with the Traveller
background as written?  I would say the answer is no.  That
limited communications is such a fundamental part of Traveller,
that you can\'t make them easier without fundamentally altering
the setting and introducing inconsistencies.

There is also some discussion as to whether the rules can be
interpreted as allowing them and wether the one or two mentions
of them makes them "canon".

