I think your numbers are a little high, but more importantly you\'re not
taking the ship\'s thrust rating into account. A Rampart (M-6) launched
immediately after jump breakout from an AHL (M-2) will correct its vector
long before its mothership does.


> In many cases, this vector
>set-up is subsumed within the voyage from the starport to the jump point;

It tacks a few hours (at most) onto transit time, and clever navigators
will try to breakout from jump so that residual V works for them, moving
them towards the destination. In most situations, GM\'s can ignore
this extra (or reduced) time -- it isn\'t important.

