    'topic' => 'TNE is dead ... long live Traveller!',
    'body' => 'Well, it certainly looks as if TNE is effectively dead ... a shame, as the
game system was, in many ways, the best yet at a character level; but
*anything* to get rid of the stupidity of Virus! OK! OK! I know, evidently
there\'s a plan to do something in the Virus era several years down the track -
but, lets face it, there are really only two realistic possibilities here -

1) The stuff that\'s on the publication list will be so successful that the bulk
of players, new and old, will be already committed to a particular era *well*
before any TNE specific stuff is released, making it pretty much an also ran.

2) The stuff that\'s on the publication list will be an abysmal (or lesser)
failure ... and let\'s hope not! ... and TNE stuff will simply never get to be
republished at all.

Is this gloating? Yep, probably! I\'m just tickled pink that Marc Miller seems
to think that Virus is as big a loser as I\'ve always thought it was! Is it
premature ... well, who knows? I hope that Traveller #4 is such a huge success
that TNE is just forgotten completely in the rush to publish new products for
other, more believable and more interesting, periods.

However, a couple of questions that haven\'t been dealt with in the posts --

1) Does the new system go back to Thruster Plates for MDrives? (It seems to
imply it does, but doesn\'t actually say it) Or are HePlaR engines still the
way to go?

2) Any further details on the Greg Porter\'s role? How free a hand is he going
to have to design the FF&S-like supplement? Or is he going to have to follow
some sort of restrictive (?) guidelines set by previous stuff?

Phil
