    'id' => '<199603092113.QAA25335@Mithril.MPGN.COM>',
    'file' => 'XBOAT96/XBT96555.TXT',
    'year' => 1996,
    'from' => 'Susan M. Shock',
    'topic' => 'Virus and the New Traveller',
    'body' => '   Nothing was said about Virus being dead, or about Marc Miller hating it.
Next month (hopefully), Marc will be able to attend, and maybe then his
views will be known. The plans are to release a sourcebook covering the
Virus Era 2-3 years down the road, MAYBE SOONER. The reason Marc chose to go
to Year 0 (which, I might point out, is not the Classic Traveller setting or
the MegaTraveller setting either...) is unknown to me, but I suspect it\'s
because he has a desire to detail all of Traveller history, and what better
way to start than with the beginning of the Third Imperium? This setting
offers some of the same advantages as the TNE setting (exploration of
charted but effectively unknown space; more adventure posibilities beyond
the smuggling/military activities) but without Virus to annoy people. I
myself never disliked Virus, and all indications are that it will remain
part of the "canon" (God, I hate that term!), but this way we can all have
a Traveller we can live with.
   Gloating is unbecoming, by the way.
