    'from' => 'DUpton@vtrnntov.telecom.com.au',
    'body' => '
Jo Grant/DUB/Lotus <Jo_Grant/DUB/Lotus.LOTUSINT@crd.lotus.com> writes:

 ----
Massimo writes:
>The original CT was introduced few years after the first landing on the
moon.
>I remember the emotional impact of that landing.
>Everybody was interested in space. Now some have a  moderate interest in
>space.
  Hmm. I think it is more to the point that Traveller emerged right around
the
time that _Star Wars_ was released. This probably had a much greater
impact.
 ----

Back in Challenge 50 or so Marc Miller wrote that watching Star Wars
provided a lot of the inspiration for Traveller. A lot of the rest seems to
have come from Asimov\'s Foundation.

Which probably explains the emphasis on players travelling about in 200 ton
free traders trying to stay one step ahead of Imperial money lenders etc.

Traveller appeared at a time when virtually all RPG\'s were generic in nature
and the notion of doing the game of a movie was beyond the means of most
game companies.

 ----
Now they are talking about a new _Star Wars_ release. If it has the same
impact of the first series (and it is, more or less, a generation later),
then _this_ is the audience they have a good chance at targeting...
    Showing my age...
                Jo
 ----

Unfortunately for Traveller there now exists a very popular Star Wars
roleplaying game that will get most of the benefit from any new Star Wars
films etc.

Any new Star Wars films will have much less impact than the first one.
You would recall that before SW there was nothing quite like it and after it
there have been heaps of imitators. Battlestar Galactica springs to mind as
something that appeared soon after SW, attempting to piggyback on SW
success, but that was quite Star Trek like as well...

Django, remembering the first time he saw SW back in its first run in the
cinema.

" I\'ve got this idea for a film. It\'s a sci-fi that\'s a sort of western in
space, with the sword fighting and mysticism of a samurai flick, and
sandwiching in space dogfights as if from the Battle of Britain and a heroic
Dambusters style attack on the bad guys. Oh and the bad guys all look and
behave like the Nazis in a war movie too."

".... Damn someone beat me to it!" :)
