To: xboat@mpgn.com


Dear Folks -

1.FLEET JUMPING IN MT

This is actually in _Megatraveller Journal #2_, not number 1. (But thank you
Mark, for pointing me in the right direction. I *knew* I read that reference
somewhere, but it escaped my filing system. I\'ve now noted it in big letters!).

2.INVADING FLEETS

Actually, you can use an easy trick to ignore all need for your calculations.
The SOM says that a good navigator can program a jump vector so that it evens
out your momentum in relation to the destination system, even reducing your
relative velocities to zero.

However, I think that this trick should at least increase the navigation
difficulty by one level!

3.CYBERWARE

"Computer Implants", J. Andrew Keith, _JTAS_ #22, GDW, USA, 1985, pp 9-12, 38.

"Medical Digest - Replacement Body Parts: Prosthetics, Bionics, Regrowth and
Cloning", Parts 1-3, Author?, _Traveller\'s Digest_ #12-14, DGP, USA, 19??

