    'topic' => 'Vehicle Computers',
    'body' => 'Speaking of computers (see earlier post "Re: Robots"), has anyone else
found it necessary to introduce a computer smaller than a model 0?  When
trying to design even inexpensive grav vehicles (less than kCr100) I
invariably end up requiring either way too many electronic panels (need
a computer to use any kind of linked panel) or a model 0 computer (or
two) that increases the price by a third.

My solution was to introduce a "minimal" computer that would allow the
use of the better panels, but have a CP multiplier of 1.  (It would just
provide networking between the panels and devices.)  For the interested,
the stats I invented for such a minimal computer are Volume: .05 kl,
Masss: .025 ton, Power: .0005 MW, Price: Cr2500, CP Mult: x1(allows
linked/dynamic panels).

Comments?

--
