>compatible lifeforms, ergo they will develop diseases capable of preying on
>Terran descended life-forms

(See above comments.)

>and this makes a nonsense of the argument
>that the Vilani were still suffering from any real medical lag when they met
>the Terrans.

Actually, even ignoring the problems with your position I mentioned above,
the fact that they Valani are trying to explain something that not only
doesn\'t make sense (and in fact, never happened), ie how they arose on
Vland and how they fit in, is going to fundamentally cripple progress.
