Gee I guess I"m so laking in "basic scientific" knowledge as to only
be able to get a Ph. D. in Chemistry from M.I.T. (it\'s a "small
technical school in Massachusetts, perhaps you\'ve heard of it) and
been able to find employment as a scientist for 10 years (over 4
of which have been working in the field in question).  I guess
this pales in significance compared to what Mr. McGregor has
been able to pick up reading in his spare time.
[End of sarcasm.]

Your arrogance is impressive.  However, I would suggest that it
might be appropriate to show a little more humility toward your
own limitations and respect for those whom might disagree with you.

>As I understand it, Viruses are based on incomplete RNA strands that have to
>use human (or terran animal) cells to complete their "life" cycle. How can you
>not see that such a development *must* be the logical corollary of Panspermia?
>If all life has been spread evenly throughout the galaxy from a single source,
