>must have viruses as well.

Ironically, this is an important point (which I\'ve been trying to make)
that does support the Vilani vulnerability to disease and does nothing
to require panspermia.  The fact is that the premise is that virus
for humans _aren\'t_ compatible with life from other biospheres.  This
means that you _don\'t_ have to invoke panspermia (or ancients, or
anything else) and it gives you exactly what was described, a population
that has been sheltered from disease until it comes in contact with the
terran biosphere.

>And, in any case, does it say that the Plague of
>Duskir was only a virus?

I\'ve never seen anything that said either way.  Which means there
is nothing in it being viral to discredit the premise.  Now
