Is it arrogance to point out flaws in GDW\'s background? Well, perhaps.
Remember, we are not substantially arguing chemisty (or biochemistry) here, we
are arguing how it affects a very specific matter ... Vilani medical knowledge
at the time they contact Terra.

> >As I understand it, Viruses are based on incomplete RNA strands that have to
> >use human (or terran animal) cells to complete their "life" cycle. How can yo
> >not see that such a development *must* be the logical corollary of Panspermia
> >If all life has been spread evenly throughout the galaxy from a single source
> >it cannot be other than that most (if not all) worlds where it has been sprea
